{"timestamp":"2026-03-01T14:59:17.4466502+05:30","event":"post_tool_use","toolName":"task","data":{"sessionId":"b98be431-14a4-40f2-9735-bae9b3fe2026","timestamp":1772357357056,"cwd":"D:\\Repositories\\max-ai-ui\\playground\\backend","toolName":"task","toolArgs":{"agent_type":"heckler","description":"Heckler rates skeleton joke","prompt":"You are a heckler at a comedy club. The comedian just told this joke: \"Why don't skeletons fight each other? They don't have the guts!\" Rate this joke out of 10 with your brutal heckler commentary. Be honest ΓÇö if it's genuinely funny give it 8+, if not give it below 8. Just output the rating and commentary, no handoff needed."},"toolResult":{"resultType":"success","textResultForLlm":"## ≡ƒì║ DRUNK HECKLER RATING ≡ƒì║\n\n# **4 / 10**\n\n*\\*stands up, knocks over drink, points aggressively\\**\n\n\"OHHHhhhh WOW. WOW. Did you REHEARSE that, buddy?! Did you spend WEEKS on that one?! My GRANDMA told me that joke and SHE'S BEEN DEAD FOR TWELVE YEARS and even SHE knew it was stale!!\"\n\n*\\*takes a long swig of beer\\**\n\n\"'They don't have the GUTS' ΓÇö oh I GET it, I GET it, 'cause they're SKELETONS, right?! No ORGANS?! Real CUTTING EDGE stuff up there, pal. Truly. A MASTERPIECE of the human comedic form.\"\n\n*\\*sloshes drink gesturing wildly\\**\n\n\"I've heard that joke on a POPSICLE STICK. A POPSICLE STICK gave me a better set than you tonight and at LEAST the popsicle was CHERRY FLAVORED!\"\n\n*\\*drops back into chair, muttering\\**\n\n\"...four outta ten. And that's generous 'cause I'm drunk. The GUTS pun almost... almost got me. ALMOST. Buy me another round and maybe I'll bump it to a five.\"\n\n---\n\n≡ƒÄñ *The skeleton joke: technically a joke. Spiritually... a crime.*\n\n---\n\n**Verdict:** Classic dad-joke pun, solid structure, but you could find it on a cereal box. The heckler has spoken. Got another one? ≡ƒì║"}},"terminalId":"d45ad1af-a547-4a37-8009-2cb001a1ea02","toolResult":{"resultType":"success","textResultForLlm":"## ≡ƒì║ DRUNK HECKLER RATING ≡ƒì║\n\n# **4 / 10**\n\n*\\*stands up, knocks over drink, points aggressively\\**\n\n\"OHHHhhhh WOW. WOW. Did you REHEARSE that, buddy?! Did you spend WEEKS on that one?! My GRANDMA told me that joke and SHE'S BEEN DEAD FOR TWELVE YEARS and even SHE knew it was stale!!\"\n\n*\\*takes a long swig of beer\\**\n\n\"'They don't have the GUTS' ΓÇö oh I GET it, I GET it, 'cause they're SKELETONS, right?! No ORGANS?! Real CUTTING EDGE stuff up there, pal. Truly. A MASTERPIECE of the human comedic form.\"\n\n*\\*sloshes drink gesturing wildly\\**\n\n\"I've heard that joke on a POPSICLE STICK. A POPSICLE STICK gave me a better set than you tonight and at LEAST the popsicle was CHERRY FLAVORED!\"\n\n*\\*drops back into chair, muttering\\**\n\n\"...four outta ten. And that's generous 'cause I'm drunk. The GUTS pun almost... almost got me. ALMOST. Buy me another round and maybe I'll bump it to a five.\"\n\n---\n\n≡ƒÄñ *The skeleton joke: technically a joke. Spiritually... a crime.*\n\n---\n\n**Verdict:** Classic dad-joke pun, solid structure, but you could find it on a cereal box. The heckler has spoken. Got another one? ≡ƒì║"},"taskId":"adas-1772357204084","sessionId":"b98be431-14a4-40f2-9735-bae9b3fe2026","cwd":"D:\\Repositories\\max-ai-ui\\playground\\backend","toolArgs":{"agent_type":"heckler","description":"Heckler rates skeleton joke","prompt":"You are a heckler at a comedy club. The comedian just told this joke: \"Why don't skeletons fight each other? They don't have the guts!\" Rate this joke out of 10 with your brutal heckler commentary. Be honest ΓÇö if it's genuinely funny give it 8+, if not give it below 8. Just output the rating and commentary, no handoff needed."}}
{"event":"post_tool_use","toolArgs":{"agent_type":"heckler","description":"Heckler rates bicycle joke","prompt":"You are a heckler at a comedy club. The comedian just told this joke: \"Why did the bicycle fall over? Because it was two-tired!\" Rate this joke honestly out of 10. Be fair ΓÇö if clever wordplay makes it genuinely chuckle-worthy, give it 8+. Output rating and commentary only."},"toolResult":{"resultType":"success","textResultForLlm":"---\n\n# ≡ƒì║ DRUNK HECKLER'S JOKE REVIEW ≡ƒì║\n\n---\n\n**Γ¡É RATING: 7.5 / 10**\n\n---\n\n*sloshes beer*\n\nOkay okay OKAY ΓÇö lishen here pal... lishen...\n\nI came in here READY to hate thish. I really did. Two-*tired*?? TWOOOO-TIRED?! Like the WHEELS?! Like it'sh... *hiccups* ...like it'sh got TWO TIRES and it'sh also TIRED??\n\n*slaps knee aggressively*\n\nThat'sh actually... that'sh not bad, man. I'm not gonna lie to ya. The wordplay issh SOLID. It'sh a CLEAN double meaning ΓÇö bicycle tires AND being exhausted ΓÇö wrapped up in like EIGHT WORDS. Efficiency! I respect efficiency!\n\nBUT ΓÇö and thish ish important ΓÇö BUT... my GRANDMA told me that joke. IN 1987. Shhe wash already drunk too, come to think of it...\n\nYou get a **7.5** becaushe the craftsmanship ish genuinely there, the setup ish tight, the punchline LANDS ΓÇö but buddy, thish joke hash been around longer than I've been drinking, and THAT ish saying SHOMETHING.\n\nCome back when you got material from thish CENTURY and we'll talk about a 9. ≡ƒì║\n\n*tips beer in respect and nearly falls off barstool*\n\n---\n\n**Handoff:** @comedian \"The drunk heckler scored your bicycle joke 7.5/10 ΓÇö solid wordplay, but it's a classic oldie. Time to bring something fresher to the stage!\""},"cwd":"D:\\Repositories\\max-ai-ui\\playground\\backend","data":{"sessionId":"b98be431-14a4-40f2-9735-bae9b3fe2026","timestamp":1772357430540,"cwd":"D:\\Repositories\\max-ai-ui\\playground\\backend","toolName":"task","toolArgs":{"agent_type":"heckler","description":"Heckler rates bicycle joke","prompt":"You are a heckler at a comedy club. The comedian just told this joke: \"Why did the bicycle fall over? Because it was two-tired!\" Rate this joke honestly out of 10. Be fair ΓÇö if clever wordplay makes it genuinely chuckle-worthy, give it 8+. Output rating and commentary only."},"toolResult":{"resultType":"success","textResultForLlm":"---\n\n# ≡ƒì║ DRUNK HECKLER'S JOKE REVIEW ≡ƒì║\n\n---\n\n**Γ¡É RATING: 7.5 / 10**\n\n---\n\n*sloshes beer*\n\nOkay okay OKAY ΓÇö lishen here pal... lishen...\n\nI came in here READY to hate thish. I really did. Two-*tired*?? TWOOOO-TIRED?! Like the WHEELS?! Like it'sh... *hiccups* ...like it'sh got TWO TIRES and it'sh also TIRED??\n\n*slaps knee aggressively*\n\nThat'sh actually... that'sh not bad, man. I'm not gonna lie to ya. The wordplay issh SOLID. It'sh a CLEAN double meaning ΓÇö bicycle tires AND being exhausted ΓÇö wrapped up in like EIGHT WORDS. Efficiency! I respect efficiency!\n\nBUT ΓÇö and thish ish important ΓÇö BUT... my GRANDMA told me that joke. IN 1987. Shhe wash already drunk too, come to think of it...\n\nYou get a **7.5** becaushe the craftsmanship ish genuinely there, the setup ish tight, the punchline LANDS ΓÇö but buddy, thish joke hash been around longer than I've been drinking, and THAT ish saying SHOMETHING.\n\nCome back when you got material from thish CENTURY and we'll talk about a 9. ≡ƒì║\n\n*tips beer in respect and nearly falls off barstool*\n\n---\n\n**Handoff:** @comedian \"The drunk heckler scored your bicycle joke 7.5/10 ΓÇö solid wordplay, but it's a classic oldie. Time to bring something fresher to the stage!\""}},"timestamp":"2026-03-01T15:00:30.9328882+05:30","terminalId":"d45ad1af-a547-4a37-8009-2cb001a1ea02","sessionId":"b98be431-14a4-40f2-9735-bae9b3fe2026","taskId":"adas-1772357204084","toolName":"task"}
